SUMMARY: One of the nation's top cybersecurity officials said state election workers in Wisconsin and Michigan have told her they're "pleased" with the federal government's support leading up the 2022 midterm elections, while some state officials say they're not getting enough.

TITLE: Permanent Daylight Saving Time will hurt our health, experts say
SUMMARY: Daylight Saving Time all year round? There's a push by the US Senate to make it so, but it's a terrible idea that may ruin our health, sleep experts say.

TITLE: RNC chairwoman says Republicans will accept election results after letting 'the process play out'
SUMMARY: Republican National Committee Chairwoman Ronna McDaniel said Sunday that candidates from her party would accept the results of the midterm elections after letting "the process play out."

TITLE: Former MoviePass executives face fraud charges
SUMMARY: MoviePass's former CEO and the leader of its former parent company have been indicted on securities fraud charges for deceiving investors on the sustainability and profitability of the company's movie-a-day subscription model, according to a Department of Justice release on Friday.

TITLE: At least 2 dead, multiple people missing after tornadoes strike Oklahoma, Texas and Arkansas, officials say
SUMMARY: At least two people have been killed, and multiple people are missing after tornadoes hit Oklahoma, Texas and Arkansas late Friday, damaging homes and knocking out power for thousands as officials launch search and rescue efforts.

TITLE: Klobuchar pushes back against Newsom's claim that Democrats are 'getting crushed on narrative' by Republicans
SUMMARY: Democratic Sen. Amy Klobuchar on Sunday pushed back on California Gov. Gavin Newsom's argument that their party is "getting crushed on narrative" by Republicans and right-wing media outlets.

TITLE: Sharon Lokedi and Evans Chebet complete Kenyan double at New York City Marathon
SUMMARY: Kenya's Sharon Lokedi was a surprise winner of the women's New York City Marathon on Sunday, while Evans Chebet won the men's race to complete a Kenyan double.

TITLE: 9 people are hospitalized after a shooting outside a bar in Philadelphia, police say
SUMMARY: Authorities are seeking multiple people suspected of firing into a crowd outside a Philadelphia bar Saturday night, wounding at least nine, police said.

TITLE: Italy's Pecco Bagnaia takes historic MotoGP title for Ducati
SUMMARY: Francesco 'Pecco' Bagnaia fired his Ducati to an historic MotoGP title on Sunday, in front of 170,380 fans at the Ricardo Tormo circuit in Valencia, Spain.

TITLE: Russia's war in Ukraine
SUMMARY: Iran publicly acknowledged for the first time that it supplied a "limited" number of drones to Russia. Tehran had denied Western intelligence on the weapons for weeks. Follow live updates here.

TITLE: Teenager Holger Rune shocks Novak Djokovic to claim Paris Masters title
SUMMARY: Teenager Holger Rune stunned Novak Djokovic in the final of the Paris Masters on Sunday, winning 3-6 6-3 7-5 against the 21-time grand slam champion.

TITLE: Workers vote against first unionizing effort at Home Depot
SUMMARY: Workers at a Home Depot in Philadelphia overwhelmingly voted against becoming the first store in the chain to be represented by a union.

TITLE: Conspiracy theories are predictable. Here are some of the ones you'll see on Election Day
SUMMARY: This Election Day, the overwhelming majority of Americans will perform their civic duty and vote without a problem. But in the age of social media and a concerted effort by some to undermine faith in American elections, it's the irregularities that often get the attention.

TITLE: Three presidents descend on Pennsylvania in a major day for one of the nation's most closely watched Senate contests
SUMMARY: Three presidents -- one sitting and two former -- descended on Pennsylvania Saturday for a final-stretch midterm push that underscored the stakes of one of the nation's most closely watched Senate races.

TITLE: The Oklahoma City Zoo is asking for help naming 4 adorable lion cubs
SUMMARY: The Oklahoma City Zoo is asking the public to help choose names for its new litter of African lion cubs.

TITLE: Kari Lake's campaign headquarters receives 'suspicious' mail containing white powder
SUMMARY: An envelope containing "suspicious white powder" was received Saturday at the campaign headquarters of the Republican nominee for governor in Arizona.

TITLE: Amy Schumer's son was hospitalized with RSV, comedian reveals
SUMMARY: Comedian and actress Amy Schumer has revealed that her young son, Gene, was admitted to the emergency room this week with RSV.

TITLE: Twitter delays $8 'blue check' verification plan until after the midterms
SUMMARY: Twitter is delaying the rollout of account verifications for its paid Twitter Blue subscription plan until after the midterm elections, a source with knowledge of the decision confirmed to CNN.

TITLE: Paxlovid reduces risk of long Covid, Veterans Affairs study finds
SUMMARY: Paxlovid, the antiviral pill that reduces the risk of hospitalization and death from Covid-19, also reduces the risk of long Covid, according to a new study by researchers at the US Department of Veterans Affairs.
